b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29135.htm)  [Next](sbe29137.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KA _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 3.\n\n1 1. He then should recite for himself (the following texts, viz.) the _Ri_\n_k_ as, the Ya _g_ us, the Samans, the Atharvan and A\xe1\xb9\x85giras hymns, the Brahma\n_n_ as, the Kalpa (Sutras), the Gathas, the (texts in honour of kings and\nheroes, called) Nara _s_ a _m_ sis, the Itihasas and Pura _n_ as.\n\n2\\. In that he recites the _Ri_ _k_ as, he thereby satiates the gods with\noblations of milk\xc2\x97in that (he recites) the Ya _g_ us, with oblations of\nghee\xc2\x97the Samans, with oblations of honey\xc2\x97the Atharvan and A\xe1\xb9\x85giras hymns, with\noblations of Soma\xc2\x97the Brahma _n_ as, Kalpas, Gathas, Nara _s_ a _m_ sis,\nItihasas and Pura _n_ as, with oblations of ambrosia.\n\np. 219\n\n3\\. In that he recites the _Ri_ _k_ as, rivers of milk flow, as a funeral\noblation, to his Fathers. In that (he recites) the Ya _g_ us, rivers of\nghee\xc2\x97the Samans, rivers of honey\xc2\x97the Atharvan and A\xe1\xb9\x85giras hymns, rivers of\nSoma\xc2\x97the Brahma _n_ as, Kalpas, Gathas, Nara _s_ a _m_ sis, Itihasas and Pura\n_n_ as, rivers of ambrosia.\n\n4\\. After he has recited (those texts) as far as he thinks fit, he should\nfinish with the following (verse),\n\n'Adoration to Brahman! Adoration be to Agni! Adoration to the Earth! Adoration\nto the Herbs! Adoration to the Voice! Adoration to the Lord of the Voice!\nAdoration I bring to great Vish _n_ u!'\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[218:1](sbe29136.htm#fr_529) 3, 1. On this and the following paragraphs comp.\nchiefly _S_ atapatha Brahma _n_ a XI, 5, 6. Other enumerations, contained in\nthe Veda itself, of the texts that were considered as forming the Veda or as\nattached to the body of the Veda, are found in the _S_ atapatha Brahma _n_ a\nXIV, 5, 4, 10 (Sacred Books, XV, 111), and in the _Kh_ andogya Upanishad VII,\n1 (Sacred Books, I, 109)\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 4](sbe29137.htm)\n\n"